{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 11:05:05.854334", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device(s): leaf_router_0_0\n- Root cause: bgp_hijacking\n\nRationale summary:\nleaf_router_0_0 originated an unauthorized, more-specific route 10.0.1.0/25 (configured on its loopback), which was propagated via BGP and preferred over the legitimate 10.0.1.0/24 on leaf_router_0_1. Due to longest-prefix-match, traffic to 10.0.1.2 was steered to the wrong leaf and effectively blackholed, causing HTTP failures while control-plane BGP remained healthy.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2104, "output_tokens": 139, "total_tokens": 2243, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
